The paper presents a framework for humanoid gait generation using MPC, which involves control and robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed method also incorporates machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) to generate omnidirectional motion commands. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of preview information and decision-making algorithms (cs.AI) to anticipate future ZMP velocities.
